FlorML is an XML schema for marking up legacy and modern taxonomic works, such as floras and faunas.

AVAILABILITY:
FlorML can be downloaded from these two Github repos:
https://github.com/thoha/FlorML (preferred, most up-to-date)
https://github.com/naturalis/FlorML

MANUAL:
Documentation is available on request. Basic instructions are included in the XML schema.


AUTHORS:
Thomas Hamann
Andreas Müller

CITATION:
Please cite this work appropriately:

Hamann, T., Müller, A., Roos, M.C., Sosef, M. & E. Smets. Detailed mark-up of semi-monographic legacy taxonomic works using FlorML. 2014. Taxon 63 (2): 377-393. 


